latestPosts.caption:
Blueland was founded by a mom, for moms, when our CEO and Co-Founder, @spaiji, discovered the water she used to mix her son’s formula was contaminated with microplastics. She set out to reduce her family’s plastic exposure, and from there Blueland was born—a company on a mission to create safe, sustainable alternatives to the plastic products we use in our home every day.

Most traditional cleaners are over 90% water and come packaged in single-use plastic. At Blueland, we’ve reimagined this with concentrated, plastic-free cleaning tablets wrapped in compostable paper, made with certified clean, effective ingredients. From laundry and dishwasher tablets to toilet bowl cleaners, we’re committed to making sustainable products the standard, keeping microplastics out of our water and landfills. 💙

Powerful clean, 100% plastic-free ✨ In the earliest days of building Blueland, we realized that everything was packaged in plastic packaging because so many of the formulas are liquid. For example, traditional laundry detergent is often over 90% water. We knew if we could make products in dry formats, we could eliminate the unnecessary water, harsh chemicals and package them in compostable paper. ✨ Voila! ✨ Smaller, lighter products that are 100% plastic-free and work just as well as  conventional cleaners.

Not-so-fun fact: In the U.S., cleaning products aren’t required to list every ingredient in their formula—but we do. At Blueland, we believe in complete transparency, which is why you’ll always find our full (clean and 100% plastic-free!) ingredient lists on every product page of our website—as well as right here for everyone to see. Because you deserve to know exactly what you’re using in your own home around those you love most.

latestPosts.caption:
For everyone who said that they would get around to spring cleaning... we hate to have to inform you that summer is here ☀️

Your summer cleaning scavenger hunt: 
☑️ Put your toothbrush holder in the dishwasher
☑️ Soak your shower head in 1/2 of a tablet of toilet cleaner
☑️ Vacuum and deodorize your mattress with oxi laundry booster 
☑️ Spray your washing machine down with multi-surface cleaner
☑️ Sprinkle and swipe powder dish soap in the kitchen sink

We asked the girls why we should care about the planet 🌎⭐️

 and here’s what they had to say...

We love teaching them to honor the Earth and that our impact really matters. No matter how messy the house gets (hello 3 kids) we’re set on only using cleaner formulas that are 100% microplastic-free and have no harsh chemicals whatsoever.  Only the best for our fam. #bluelandpartner

The 101º forecast gives us the perfect excuse to stay in and clean 🧼
